page.title: 17COUNTRY PARKS
page.content: {DINTON PASTURES COUNTRY PARK}OPENED IN 1979. SINCE THEN OVER 150 SPECIES OF{BIRDS}HAVE BEEN SPOTTED. THESE INCLUDE COOTS,LITTLE RINGED PLOVER,GREBE,MALLARD,WHITE SWAN,CANADA GOOSE,HERON,KINGFISHER,TERN,GADWALL AND SANDMARTIN.IN THE{RIVERS AND {LAKES}THERE ARE CHUB,BARBLE,ROACH, BREAM,PIKE,PERCH,GUDGEON,FROGS,WATER SPIDERS,TOADS,FAIRY SHRIMPS,EELS,WATER SKATERS,CADDIS FLY,MAY FLY,DIVING BEETLES,WATER SCORPIONS,STICKLEBACKS AND DRAGONFLY.BULRUSHES ARE NOW LOSING GROUND TO THE COMMON REED. THE AREA WAS{POLLUTED}BY INDUSTRIAL AND DOMESTIC WASTE,BUT THIS IS BEING CLEARED.1500 NATIVE TREES HAVE BEEN PLANTED AND THERE IS A{WILD FLOWER {NURSERY.}THE{LODDON LILY}IS NOW VERY RARE.HEDGEHOGS AND FOXES ARE AMONGST THE RETURNING WILDLIFE.
